author: @willgale8889
text: Building and installing the object detection API does work, you just have to change the import at the top from:  "from utils import label_map_util from utils import visualization_utils as vis_util"  to  "from object_detection.utils import label_map_util From object_detection.utils import visualization_utils as vis_util" (And any other things from utils you want)  The first one I think is looking for the "utils" folder that is in the object detection API, but it isn't there when running this script from a different directory (unless you copy and paste the whole folder) but once it is built and installed it puts the object detection folder in your site-packages meaning to access it you just need to add "object_detection." to whatever you want to access. When I first tried building/installing the object detection API, it didn't work and after changing these lines of code it worked fine.  If this wasn't the problem then ignore everything I just said. (Great series by the way)
